(47, 1, '2015-06-08 19:08:07', '2015-06-08 19:08:07', '[et_pb_section fullwidth=\"on\" specialty=\"off\"][et_pb_fullwidth_slider admin_label=\"Fullwidth Slider\" show_arrows=\"on\" show_pagination=\"on\" auto=\"off\" parallax=\"off\" parallax_method=\"off\"][et_pb_slide heading=\"About Masjid Suffah\" background_image=\"http://www.masjidsuffah.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/headerimage2.jpg\" background_color=\"#ffffff\" alignment=\"center\" background_layout=\"dark\" allow_player_pause=\"off\" /][/et_pb_fullwidth_slider][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section][et_pb_row][et_pb_column type=\"2_3\"][et_pb_text admin_label=\"Text\" background_layout=\"light\" text_orientation=\"left\"]\n<h1>Educate. Cultivate. Serve.</h1>\nMasjid Suffah is a non-profit religious organization established in 2015 to provide a place of worship for Muslims residing in and around Kennesaw.\n\nMasjid Suffah is named after the Ashab al-Suffah, the People of the Porch. The Ashab al-Suffah were a group of companions of the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) who sat on the porch of the masjid (mosque). They devoted their lives to studying Islam. Learning at the feet of the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) allowed the People of the Porch to cultivate a deep understanding of Islam within themselves, which allowed them to serve Allah and serve the community at large. At Masjid Suffah, we hope to revive the spirit of the Ashab al-Suffah through education, cultivation, and service.\n\n[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type=\"1_3\"][et_pb_signup admin_label=\"Subscribe\" provider=\"mailchimp\" mailchimp_list=\"cef8ebdaab\" aweber_list=\"none\" title=\"Sign up for the Masjid Suffah newsletter\" button_text=\"Sign Up\" use_background_color=\"off\" background_color=\"#7EBEC5\" background_layout=\"light\" text_orientation=\"left\" /][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row][et_pb_column type=\"1_2\"][et_pb_image admin_label=\"Image\" src=\"http://www.masjidsuffah.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/vision.jpg\" alt=\"Vision of Masjid Suffah serving the Kennesaw muslim community\" show_in_lightbox=\"off\" url_new_window=\"off\" animation=\"fade_in\" sticky=\"off\" /][et_pb_text admin_label=\"Text\" background_layout=\"light\" text_orientation=\"left\"]At Masjid Suffah, our vision is to create a vibrant Muslim community who lives according to the Quran and Sunnah (teachings of the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him), striving to build a bridge of understanding between people of all faiths.[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type=\"1_2\"][et_pb_image admin_label=\"Image\" src=\"http://www.masjidsuffah.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/mission.jpg\" alt=\"Vision of Masjid Suffah serving the Kennesaw muslim community\" show_in_lightbox=\"off\" url_new_window=\"off\" animation=\"fade_in\" sticky=\"off\" /][et_pb_text admin_label=\"Text\" background_layout=\"light\" text_orientation=\"left\"]The Suffa Dawat Center in Kennesaw would be committed to the Islamic way of life based on the Quran and the life example (Sunnah) of the Prophet Muhammad (pbuh). We shall strive to serve as a center for religious development, social, educational, economic and cultural enrichment. We believe in the oneness of Allah and the oneness of humanity. We are committed to promoting excellence in community life and human dignity throughout our neighborhoods in general and particularly in the city of Kennesaw by promoting the real essence of Islam.[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section]', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-06-08 19:08:07', '2015-06-08 19:08:07', '', 2, 'http://www.masjidsuffah.com/uncategorized/2-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
