(73, 1, '2015-06-08 19:09:37', '2015-06-08 19:09:37', '[et_pb_section fullwidth=\"on\" specialty=\"off\"][et_pb_fullwidth_slider admin_label=\"Fullwidth Slider\" show_arrows=\"on\" show_pagination=\"on\" auto=\"off\" parallax=\"off\" parallax_method=\"off\"][et_pb_slide heading=\"About Masjid Suffah\" background_image=\"http://www.masjidsuffah.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/headerimage2.jpg\" background_color=\"#ffffff\" alignment=\"center\" background_layout=\"dark\" allow_player_pause=\"off\" /][/et_pb_fullwidth_slider][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section][et_pb_row][et_pb_column type=\"2_3\"][et_pb_text admin_label=\"Text\" background_layout=\"light\" text_orientation=\"left\"]\r\n<h1>Educate. Cultivate. Serve.</h1>\r\nMasjid Suffah is a non-profit religious organization established in 2015 to provide a place of worship for Muslims residing in and around Kennesaw.\r\n\r\nMasjid Suffah is named after the Ashab al-Suffah, the People of the Porch. The Ashab al-Suffah were a group of companions of the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) who sat on the porch of the masjid (mosque). They devoted their lives to studying Islam. Learning at the feet of the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) allowed the People of the Porch to cultivate a deep understanding of Islam within themselves, which allowed them to serve Allah and serve the community at large. At Masjid Suffah, we hope to revive the spirit of the Ashab al-Suffah through education, cultivation, and service.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type=\"1_3\"][et_pb_signup admin_label=\"Subscribe\" provider=\"mailchimp\" mailchimp_list=\"cef8ebdaab\" aweber_list=\"none\" title=\"Sign up for the Masjid Suffah newsletter\" button_text=\"Sign Up\" use_background_color=\"off\" background_color=\"#7EBEC5\" background_layout=\"light\" text_orientation=\"left\" /][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row][et_pb_column type=\"1_2\"][et_pb_image admin_label=\"Image\" src=\"http://www.masjidsuffah.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/vision.jpg\" alt=\"Vision of Masjid Suffah serving the Kennesaw muslim community\" show_in_lightbox=\"off\" url_new_window=\"off\" animation=\"fade_in\" sticky=\"off\" /][et_pb_text admin_label=\"Text\" background_layout=\"light\" text_orientation=\"left\"]At Masjid Suffah, our vision is to create a vibrant Muslim community who lives according to the Quran and Sunnah (teachings of the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him), striving to build a bridge of understanding between people of all faiths.[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type=\"1_2\"][et_pb_image admin_label=\"Image\" src=\"http://www.masjidsuffah.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/mission.jpg\" alt=\"Vision of Masjid Suffah serving the Kennesaw muslim community\" show_in_lightbox=\"off\" url_new_window=\"off\" animation=\"fade_in\" sticky=\"off\" /][et_pb_text admin_label=\"Text\" background_layout=\"light\" text_orientation=\"left\"]<strong>Educate.</strong>\r\nThe Islamic tradition teaches that Islam is not only a religion but a way of life. To that end, Masjid Suffah is committed to serving as a center for religious education for all people. At Masjid Suffah, we believe education is the means through which one can gain knowledge and understanding of how to live his or her life.  We also hope to educate the greater Kennesaw community about the true teachings of Islam.  \r\n\r\n<strong>Cultivate. </strong>\r\nAt Masjid Suffah, we strive to cultivate a God-conscious community, guided by the principles of peace, unity, and compassion for all.  \r\n\r\n<strong>Serve. </strong>First and foremost, we, at Masjid Suffah, strive to serve our Lord. We are also devoted to serving the needs of the Muslim community, as well as our friends and neighbors in the local Kennesaw community.[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section]', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-08 19:09:37', '2015-06-08 19:09:37', '', 2, 'http://www.masjidsuffah.com/uncategorized/2-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(70, 1, '2015-06-08 18:49:45', '2015-06-08 18:49:45', '[et_pb_section fullwidth=\"on\" specialty=\"off\"][et_pb_fullwidth_slider admin_label=\"Fullwidth Slider\" show_arrows=\"on\" show_pagination=\"on\" auto=\"off\" parallax=\"off\" parallax_method=\"off\"][et_pb_slide heading=\"About Masjid Suffah\" background_image=\"http://www.masjidsuffah.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/headerimage2.jpg\" background_color=\"#ffffff\" alignment=\"center\" background_layout=\"dark\" allow_player_pause=\"off\" /][/et_pb_fullwidth_slider][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section][et_pb_row][et_pb_column type=\"2_3\"][et_pb_text admin_label=\"Text\" background_layout=\"light\" text_orientation=\"left\"]\r\n<h1>Educate. Cultivate. Serve.</h1>\r\nMasjid Suffah is a non-profit religious organization established in 2015 to provide a place of worship for Muslims residing in and around Kennesaw.\r\n\r\nMasjid Suffah is named after the Ashab al-Suffah, the People of the Porch. The Ashab al-Suffah were a group of companions of the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) who sat on the porch of the masjid (mosque). They devoted their lives to studying Islam. Learning at the feet of the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) allowed the People of the Porch to cultivate a deep understanding of Islam within themselves, which allowed them to serve Allah and serve the community at large. At Masjid Suffah, we hope to revive the spirit of the Ashab al-Suffah through education, cultivation, and service.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type=\"1_3\"][et_pb_signup admin_label=\"Subscribe\" provider=\"mailchimp\" mailchimp_list=\"cef8ebdaab\" aweber_list=\"none\" title=\"&lt;h1&gt;Keep up to update with events at Masjid Suffah&lt;/h1&gt;\" button_text=\"Sign Up\" use_background_color=\"off\" background_color=\"#7EBEC5\" background_layout=\"light\" text_orientation=\"left\" /][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row][et_pb_column type=\"1_2\"][et_pb_image admin_label=\"Image\" src=\"http://www.masjidsuffah.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/vision.jpg\" alt=\"Vision of Masjid Suffah serving the Kennesaw muslim community\" show_in_lightbox=\"off\" url_new_window=\"off\" animation=\"fade_in\" sticky=\"off\" /][et_pb_text admin_label=\"Text\" background_layout=\"light\" text_orientation=\"left\"]We want to be a vibrant faith community that appreciates the inherent worth of every individual. Organized and fully supported by all stakeholders, operation with the highest level of Shura (consultation). we envisioned ourselves a role model 21st century Masjid, which will be the center of learning for the local as well as global communities. With the support of our thriving business community, we are positioned for growth and expansion. A state-of-the-art, green and financially solvent community will nurture Islamic culture and business while fulfilling the destiny of a God-conscious community.[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type=\"1_2\"][et_pb_image admin_label=\"Image\" src=\"http://www.masjidsuffah.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/mission.jpg\" alt=\"Vision of Masjid Suffah serving the Kennesaw muslim community\" show_in_lightbox=\"off\" url_new_window=\"off\" animation=\"fade_in\" sticky=\"off\" /][et_pb_text admin_label=\"Text\" background_layout=\"light\" text_orientation=\"left\"]The Suffa Dawat Center in Kennesaw would be committed to the Islamic way of life based on the Quran and the life example (Sunnah) of the Prophet Muhammad (pbuh). We shall strive to serve as a center for religious development, social, educational, economic and cultural enrichment. We believe in the oneness of Allah and the oneness of humanity. We are committed to promoting excellence in community life and human dignity throughout our neighborhoods in general and particularly in the city of Kennesaw by promoting the real essence of Islam.[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section]', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-08 18:49:45', '2015-0