(159, 3, '2015-09-29 19:58:35', '2015-09-29 19:58:35', '<h2><em>Khatm-ul-Quran</em></h2>\r\nPlease join us in the <em>khatm-ul-Quran</em> which will be tonight <strong>Wednesday, July 15th (Ramadan 29th)</strong> inshaAllah.\r\n\r\nIsha prayer will start at 10:25pm. Dua will be approximately around 11:45 PM.\r\n\r\nPlease invite all friends and families to join us in the <em>khatm-ul-Qur\'an</em>. <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Sweets will be served after <em>taraweeh</em> prayer!</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>The Blessing of Attending the Completion of the Reading of the Quran </strong>\r\n\r\nThe Companions gave a high importance to completing the reading of the Quran. They also, in particular, would pay attention to the end of the reading and the recommended act of supplication made thereafter.\r\n\r\nThis is authentically narrated regarding Anas ibn Malik [may Allah be pleased with him], the illustrious Companion of the Prophet Muhammad (Allahs peace and blessings be upon him).\r\n\r\nImam al-Darimi narrates that, Anas ibn Malik, when he would complete a reading of the Quran, would gather his family and his children and supplicate for them. [al-Darimi, al-Sunan]\r\n\r\nImam al-Darimi also relates that Ibn Abbas (may Allah be pleased with father and son) used to appoint a man to watch over everyone reciting the Quran in the masjid, so that if someone was near completion, the man would inform Ibn Abbas, and Ibn Abbas and those in his company would go to attend the completion. [al-Darimi, al-Sunan]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Fundraising</h2>\r\n<em>Alhamdulillah</em> a very generous brother donated land to the masjid. The land is down the road from the current masjid location at <strong>6045 Pine Mountain RD Kennesaw, GA 30144</strong><strong>.</strong> The goal is to raise <strong>$800,000</strong> within two years to build the new masjid. InshaAllah after <em>isha</em> prayer there will be a short fundraiser. For more information about the property please click here.', 'Khatm-ul-Qur\'an and Eid Prayer', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'khatm-ul-quran-and-eid-prayer-3', '', '', '2015-11-13 22:13:03', '2015-11-13 22:13:03', '', 0, 'http://www.masjidsuffah.com/?p=159', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(160, 1, '2015-07-15 06:47:33', '2015-07-15 06:47:33', '<h2><em>Khatm-ul-Quran</em></h2>\r\nPlease join us in the <em>khatm-ul-Quran</em> which will be tonight <strong>Wednesday, July 15th (Ramadan 29th)</strong> inshaAllah.\r\n\r\nIsha prayer will start at 10:25pm. Dua will be approximately around 11:45 PM.\r\n\r\nPlease invite all friends and families to join us in the <em>khatm-ul-Qur\'an</em>. Sweets will be served after <em>taraweeh</em> prayer!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>The Blessing of Attending the Completion of the Reading of the Quran </strong>\r\n\r\nThe Companions gave a high importance to completing the reading of the Quran. They also, in particular, would pay attention to the end of the reading and the recommended act of supplication made thereafter.\r\n\r\nThis is authentically narrated regarding Anas ibn Malik [may Allah be pleased with him], the illustrious Companion of the Prophet Muhammad (Allahs peace and blessings be upon him).\r\n\r\nImam al-Darimi narrates that, Anas ibn Malik, when he would complete a reading of the Quran, would gather his family and his children and supplicate for them. [al-Darimi, al-Sunan]\r\n\r\nImam al-Darimi also relates that Ibn Abbas (may Allah be pleased with father and son) used to appoint a man to watch over everyone reciting the Quran in the masjid, so that if someone was near completion, the man would inform Ibn Abbas, and Ibn Abbas and those in his company would go to attend the completion. [al-Darimi, al-Sunan]\r\n<h2>Fundraising</h2>\r\n<em>Alhamdulillah</em> a very generous brother donated land to the masjid. The land is down the road from the current masjid location at <strong>6045 Pine Mountain RD Kennesaw, GA 30144</strong><strong>.</strong> The goal is to raise <strong>$800,000</strong> within two years to build the new masjid. InshaAllah after <em>isha</em> prayer there will be a short fundraiser. For more information about the property please <a href=\"http://www.masjidsuffah.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Fundraising-Flyer.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a>.\r\n<h2><em>Eid</em> Prayer</h2>\r\nIf the moon is sighted on Thursday, July 16th then inshaAllah <em>Eid</em> prayer will be <strong>at Masjid Suffah</strong> on Friday, July 17th. To accommodate the large crowd two prayers will be held:\r\n\r\n<strong>1. 8:00 AM</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>2. 8:45 AM</strong>\r\n\r\nIf the the moon is not sighted on Thursday, July 16th then inshaAllah <em>Eid</em> prayer will be held in the<strong> gym of Pine Mountain Middle School at 2720 Pine Mountain Circle Kennesaw, Georgia 30152</strong> <strong>at 8:30 AM.</strong>', 'Khatm-ul-Qur\'an and Eid Prayer', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'khatm-ul-quran-and-eid-prayer-2', '', '', '2015-11-13 22:13:41', '2015-11-13 22:13:41', '', 0, 'http://www.masjidsuffah.com/?p=160', 0, 'post', '', 0),
