(428, 1, '2016-02-12 21:47:25', '2016-02-12 21:47:25', '<h2>Bridging the Gap: The Parent-Child Relationship</h2>\r\n<div>Although there are differences between each generation, in recent times we find the gap between parents and their children to be wider than it has ever been, particularly in the US. Having been raised in different countries, many parents find it difficult to relate to the issues their children face. While raising children in the West, it is necessary that parents learn to be open minded about different ways of doing things, while always maintaining the Islamic perspective in all situations. Join us for a talk by Shaykh Ibrahim Memon Madani (teacher of resident scholar maulanaMohammed Faizan Wahid) as he explains how we as a community can learn to bridge the gap between parents and their children.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<h3><strong>This program is not at Masjid Suffah it is at Darul Arqam Institute</strong></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>Venue: Darul Arqam Institute 5365 five forks trickum Rd Lilburn, GA 30047</strong></div>\r\n<div><strong>Time: salatul maghrib (6:22 PM - salatul isha (8:00 PM)</strong></div>\r\n<div><strong>Saturday, February 13th, 2016</strong></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Shaykh Ibrahim Memon Madani was born in the blessed city of Madinah. He began his quest of knowledge at an early age, with the memorization of the Holy Quran. Shortly thereafter, he traveled to Bury, England where he completed his traditional studies at the prestigious Madrasah Arabiyya Islamiyya. Upon completion of his studies, Shaykh Ibrahim moved to the west, where he established Darul Uloom Al-Madania in Buffalo, NY, its sister branch, Darul Uloom Canada in Chatham, Ontario, and eAlim, an online distance education program catered to who want to seek authentic Islamic knowledge but are unable to attend a full-time seminary. Currently, Shaykh Ibrahim is a senior lecturer and research scholar in Darul Uloom Canada. He has given hundreds of lectures on various topics of audio recordings on various topics and has authored a number of works including, The Book of Purification, The Essentials of Jumma and The Preservation of Hadith.</div>', 'Bridging the Gap: The Parent-Child Relationship', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'bridging-the-gap-the-parent-child-relationship', '', '', '2016-02-21 16:31:23', '2016-02-21 16:31:23', '', 0, 'http://www.masjidsuffah.com/?p=428', 0, 'post', '', 0),
