(448, 3, '2016-02-21 17:25:09', '2016-02-21 17:25:09', '[et_pb_section fullwidth=\"on\" specialty=\"off\"][et_pb_fullwidth_slider admin_label=\"Fullwidth Slider\" show_arrows=\"on\" show_pagination=\"on\" auto=\"off\" parallax=\"off\" parallax_method=\"off\"][et_pb_slide heading=\"Suffah Masjid Maktab\" background_image=\"http://www.masjidsuffah.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/sliderimage_01.jpg\" background_color=\"#ffffff\" alignment=\"center\" background_layout=\"dark\" allow_player_pause=\"off\" /][/et_pb_fullwidth_slider][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section fullwidth=\"off\" specialty=\"off\"][et_pb_row][et_pb_column type=\"4_4\"][et_pb_text admin_label=\"Text\" background_layout=\"light\" text_orientation=\"left\"]\r\n\r\nMasjid Suffah Maktab\r\n\r\nDetails are as follows:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.masjidsuffah.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Admissions-Form-2015.pdf\">Click here to download Admission form</a>\r\n\r\n<strong><u>Timings:</u></strong>\r\n\r\nTuesday  Thursday (3 days)\r\n\r\n5:30  7:00 PM\r\n\r\n<strong><u>Subjects taught</u></strong>\r\n\r\nQuran recitation                  [Quranic Recitation]\r\n\r\nDuas/Surah memorization   [Memorization in Arabic]\r\n\r\nFiqh ul Islam    [Islamic Rulings]\r\n\r\nSeerah un Nabi         [Life of Nabi SAW]\r\n\r\nAkhlaaq    [Manners in Islam]\r\n\r\nAqaaid   [Beliefs of a Muslim]\r\n\r\n<strong><u>Fees</u></strong>\r\n\r\nThe fees for maktab is $50 per month. If any family is not able to pay the monthly fees the masjid will sponsor those children.\r\n\r\nWe would encourage every parent to donate monthly towards the educational expenses.\r\n\r\n<strong><u>Goals</u></strong>\r\n\r\nThe goals of the Evening Islamic Studies are to provide the children a sound foundation in their Islamic knowledge and practices, while inculcating the love of Allah and the Prophet (Allah bless him and grant him peace)\r\n\r\nThe <em>tarbiyyah</em>  (upbringing) of the students is highly emphasized.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong><u>FAQ:</u></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>From what ages are children taken?</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>Children aged 6 and up are eligible for admittance. Children 5 may be admitted upon taking an aptitude test.</em>\r\n\r\n<strong>What if I cant make it for all 3 days?</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>We encourage attendance so that there is no shortfall in the work learned. However if a child can only come for certain days we will try our best to accommodate the child</em>\r\n\r\n<strong>I would like to volunteer</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>Volunteers are always welcome. From teaching to being an aide, were always looking for dedicated and child-friendly teachers.</em>\r\n\r\n<strong>What is taught exactly?</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>We have 5 core subjects. Primarily the children are taught to read the Quran with proper pronunciation. Alongside, the supplemental subjects are detailed as follows:</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Fiqh: The child is taught the basics of Islam. How to pray, make wudu, fast etc. The goal is enable each child to have a firm grasp of the basic practices as they pertain to the ritual worship</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Seerah: Here the student is taught the life history of the Prophet (Allah bless him and grant him peace) as well a brief history of some of the earlier Prophets (All bless them and grant them peace)</em>\r\n\r\n<em>The goal is inculcate a knowledge and love for the life of the Prophet (Allah bless him and grant him peace)</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Akhlaaq: Students are taught the manners of Islam from a theoretical as well as a practical standpoint. For example how to talk, respect parents, eat, sleep, play, interact with Muslims as well as non etc</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Aqaaid: Here the children are taught beliefs that make a Muslim a Muslim, including the beliefs held about Allah, His Angels, His Books, His Messengers etc from the standpoint of the Ahl us Sunnah wal Jamaah</em>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong><strong>How do I enroll my child?</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>Simply download the application form and bring in to the Imam or any of the member of theboard.</em>\r\n\r\n<strong>How can I support the school?</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>One may be a well-wisher and keep the educational programs in ones duas (supplications) We also encourage your oral, physical and monetary support to keep the school  with the Beneficence of Allah  vibrant.</em>\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section]', 'Maktab', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '285-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-21 17:25:09', '2016-02-21 17:25:09', '', 285, 'http://www.masjidsuffah.com/uncategorized/285-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(458, 3, '2016-03-07 18:28:19', '2016-03-07 18:28:19', '<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.masjidsuffah.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/How-to-Deal-with-your-Non-Muslim-Neighbors.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-456\" src=\"http://www.masjidsuffah.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/How-to-Deal-with-your-Non-Muslim-Neighbors-232x300.jpg\" alt=\"How to Deal with your Non-Muslim Neighbors\" width=\"232\" height=\"300\" /></a></h2>\r\n<h3>How To Treat Your Non-Muslim Neighbor</h3>\r\nThe neighbor holds a special status in Islam. Islam encourages Muslims to treat their neighbors in a gentle way that reflects the true and genuine spirit of Islam as exemplified in its tolerant aspect especially with people of other faiths. It makes no difference whether the neighbors are Muslim or non-Muslim. Aishah, the Mother of the Believers, (may Allah be pleased with her) stated that she once asked the Prophet (peace and blessings be upon him), O Messenger of Allah! I have two neighbors. To whom shall I send my gifts? He said, To the one whose gate is nearer to you.\r\n\r\nIt is clear from the above Prophetic Hadith that Muslims are encouraged to not only treat our neighbors kindly, but also to exchange gifts with them. The wording of the Hadith does not indicate whether the one with whom we exchange gifts is a Muslim or not.\r\n\r\nIt was even reported that the Prophet () had a neighbor who used to harm him and insult him at every encounter. Some days elapsed without the Prophet getting his share of this mans abuse. Thinking that there must be some reason behind the mans absence, he (peace and blessings be upon him) paid him a visit and found him sick. The man wondered how the Prophet could meet his bad treatment with such great behavior. To him, such noble character as taught by Islam was completely new.\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Date:</span><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Saturday, March 12, 2016</span></h3>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Place:</span> Masjid Suffah (2750 Jiles RD Kennesaw, GA 30144)</h3>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Time:</span> After Maghrib Prayer (6:44 pm)</h3>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Food will be served!</span></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>', 'How To Treat Your Non-Muslim Neighbor', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '455-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-07 18:28:19', '2016-03-07 18:28:19', '', 455, 'http://www.masjidsuffah.com/uncategorized/455-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(460, 1, '2016-03-17 02:57:46', '2016-03-17 02:57:46', '<div>Assalaamu \'alaykum,</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Alhamdullilah, Masjid Suffah as adopted a one-mile stretch of Pine Mountain Road. We are planning, insha\'Allah, to go and clean-up this road this coming<b><span class=\"aBn\" tabindex=\"0\" data-term=\"goog_1679097618\"><span class=\"aQJ\">Saturday, March 19th</span></span></b>. We will <b>meet at Masjid Suffah at<span class=\"aBn\" tabindex=\"0\" data-term=\"goog_1679097619\"><span class=\"aQJ\">11:00 am</span></span></b>, go over some safety instructions. We are looking for male volunteers, ages 13+ (any child younger must be accompanied by an adult). This is an excellent opportunity to be civically active in our community and at the same time, gain reward from Allah Ta\'ala.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Please fill out the sheet below by <span class=\"aBn\" tabindex=\"0\" data-term=\"goog_1679097620\"><span class=\"aQJ\">Thursday</span></span> night, so we can have a head count of how many people will be attending. Please fill out the sheet individually for every person attending, even if you are from the same family.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><a href=\"http://goo.gl/forms/Zn4UDdBDoY\" target=\"_blank\">http://goo.gl/forms/Zn4UDdBDoY</a></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><img class=\"CToWUd\" src=\"https://ci6.googleusercontent.com/proxy/RnNZfQn2o2xpggJQqefCOervMbPIci5mujDPJnvl43kv6Rtxjyh5gHN_JKVzeU-aaGz3pePFgxfoAAtZJZNx8mveVTc-11j98EfuAJVcumUenA=s0-d-e1-ft#https://ssl.gstatic.com/ui/v1/icons/mail/images/cleardot.gif\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div>Please contact <a href=\"tel:%28770%29%20866-1525\" target=\"_blank\">(770) 866-1525</a> if you have any questions.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Jazakumullahu khayrun</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Masjid Suffah</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', 'Adopt-a-Mile', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'adopt-a-mile', '', '', '2016-04-17 16:36:16', '2016-04-17 16:36:16', '', 0, 'http://www.masjidsuffah.com/?p=460', 0, 'post', '', 0),
